This paper deals with the optimization of routing in wireless mesh networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper proposes the use of Particle Swarm Optimization (PSO) and Genetic Algorithm (GA), which are both artificial intelligence techniques, to solve the routing problem. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.AI and cs.SY. The paper also deals with Quality of Service (QoS) constraints, which involves the use of penalty functions, indicating that it may also be categorized under cs.IT. Finally, the paper deals with the issue of interference in wireless mesh networks, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC).
